Welcome to Arawa Lexical Database (ALeD)

This page is designed to query the database locally with SQLite. Data is loaded in memory and can take a while to load. It is intended for experimentation and exploration by advanced users familiar with SQL.

The `sqljs` library is original work by kripken (sql.js), now maintained by lovasoa.


Table schemata:
forms: id text, doculect text, value text, form text, tokens text, cogids text, tokens text, morphemes text, concept text, note text
languages: id text, doculect text, glottocode text, glottolog_name text, iso639p3code text, macroarea text, latitude text, longitude text, family text, sources text
parameters: id text, concept text, concepticon_id text, concepticon_gloss text, semantic_field text

Results will be displayed here
Additional Information

The Arawa Lexical Database (ALeD) is the first part of the Arawa Languages Resources Projet (ArLaR) to be made public. Its goal is to provide data (lexical, moprhological, and syntactic) for linguistic analysis. We invite and welcome suggestions, criticisms, and collaborators.
